heaviest_rainrate.status: The rain rate reached 27.0mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

longest_rain.status: Rain fell for 20.3 hours on 04 January 2025 (ranking 6th from our records for the longest storm) and it produced a total of 6.97mm of rain at a maximum intensity of 4.1mm per hour.  A relentless rainstorm took place on 04 January 2025, it lasted 37.2 hours and it delivered 36.8mm of rain at a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour.
